text.section:
Within 5 days after receiving the report, the local department and the appropriate law enforcement agency shall:
see the child in person;
attempt to have an on-site interview with the child's caregiver and the individual identified in the report as an individual registered under Title 11, Subtitle 7 of the Criminal Procedure Article based on the commission of an offense against a child;
decide on the safety and level of risk to the child, wherever the child is, and of other children in the household; and
decide on the safety and level of risk of other children in the care or custody of the individual identified in the report as an individual registered under Title 11, Subtitle 7 of the Criminal Procedure Article based on the commission of an offense against a child.

As part of the investigation, the local department shall:
determine whether the child is safe;
determine whether sexual abuse of the child has occurred;
if appropriate, offer services to the family; and
immediately decide whether to file a petition alleging that the child is in need of assistance.
